<subSubSection lastPageId="107" lastPageNumber="108" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="106.[151,1437,1828,2033]" lastBlockId="107.[151,1436,151,248]" lastPageId="107" lastPageNumber="108" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1828,1853]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Easily distinguished from most known congeners by shape of male palp (very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2015" box="[1283,1392,1829,1853]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="itapoa">
<emphasis box="[1283,1392,1829,1853]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">M. itapoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, cf. Huber 2015: figs 193–194; wide femur; distinctive shape of procursus; genital bulb with slightly sclerotized process and long membranous side branch), by shape of male chelicerae (
<figureCitation box="[1044,1208,1900,1925]" captionStart="FIGURES 481–488" captionStartId="109.[151,264,1929,1951]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,274,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@109.[151,1436,265,1908]" captionTargetPageId="109" captionText="FIGURES 481–488. Mesabolivar niteroi sp. n. (481–487, ZFMK Ar 19198) and M. itapoa Huber, 2015 (488, ZFMK Ar 12645).481–482.Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. 483.Left procursus, retrolateral view.484–485.Epigynum, lateral and ventral,views.487. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view.486, 488.Epigyna in posterior views.Scale lines:0.3." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202637/files/figure.png" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">Figs 481–482</figureCitation>
; distinctive pair of processes), by pair of posterior processes on female sternum, and by shape of epigynum (
<figureCitation box="[1150,1308,1936,1961]" captionStart="FIGURES 481–488" captionStartId="109.[151,264,1929,1951]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,274,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@109.[151,1436,265,1908]" captionTargetPageId="109" captionText="FIGURES 481–488. Mesabolivar niteroi sp. n. (481–487, ZFMK Ar 19198) and M. itapoa Huber, 2015 (488, ZFMK Ar 12645).481–482.Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. 483.Left procursus, retrolateral view.484–485.Epigynum, lateral and ventral,views.487. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view.486, 488.Epigyna in posterior views.Scale lines:0.3." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202637/files/figure.png" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">Figs 484–486</figureCitation>
; distinctive processes on anterior plate; rows of stronger hairs on small sclerotized plates behind epigynum); from very similar 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2015" box="[151,261,2010,2033]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="itapoa">
<emphasis box="[151,261,2010,2033]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">M. itapoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by male chelicerae (apophyses much less projecting in lateral view, compare 
<figureCitation box="[1144,1238,2008,2033]" captionStart="FIGURES 481–488" captionStartId="109.[151,264,1929,1951]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,274,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@109.[151,1436,265,1908]" captionTargetPageId="109" captionText="FIGURES 481–488. Mesabolivar niteroi sp. n. (481–487, ZFMK Ar 19198) and M. itapoa Huber, 2015 (488, ZFMK Ar 12645).481–482.Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. 483.Left procursus, retrolateral view.484–485.Epigynum, lateral and ventral,views.487. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view.486, 488.Epigyna in posterior views.Scale lines:0.3." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202637/files/figure.png" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">Fig. 482</figureCitation>
and Huber 2015: fig. 198), by anterior epigynal plate (only one pair of processes in posterior view, compare 
<figureCitation box="[1176,1335,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 481–488" captionStartId="109.[151,264,1929,1951]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,274,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@109.[151,1436,265,1908]" captionTargetPageId="109" captionText="FIGURES 481–488. Mesabolivar niteroi sp. n. (481–487, ZFMK Ar 19198) and M. itapoa Huber, 2015 (488, ZFMK Ar 12645).481–482.Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. 483.Left procursus, retrolateral view.484–485.Epigynum, lateral and ventral,views.487. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view.486, 488.Epigyna in posterior views.Scale lines:0.3." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202637/files/figure.png" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Figs 486, 488</figureCitation>
); also by shorter processes on female sternum (&lt;100 µm long vs. 150 µm in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2015" box="[902,1011,189,212]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="itapoa">
<emphasis box="[902,1011,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">M. itapoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
